#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.32"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.32:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.32:0.2"
msgid "4. Devadūtavagga"
msgstr "4. Messengers of the Gods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.32:0.3"
msgid "32. Ānandasutta"
msgstr "32. With Ānanda"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.32:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to the Buddha:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.32:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Siyā nu kho, bhante, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā imasmiñca "
"saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu, bahiddhā ca "
"sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu;"
msgstr ""
"“Could it be, sir, that a mendicant might gain a state of immersion such "
"that there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for "
"this conscious body; and no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to "
"conceit for all external stimuli;"

msgctxt "an3.32:2.2"
msgid ""
"yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato "
"ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"upasampajja vihareyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"and that they’d live having attained the freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom where ego, possessiveness, and underlying tendency to conceit are no "
"more?”"

msgctxt "an3.32:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Siyā, ānanda, bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā imasmiñca "
"saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu, bahiddhā ca "
"sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu;"
msgstr ""
"“It could be, Ānanda, that a mendicant gains a state of immersion such that "
"they have no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this "
"conscious body; and no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to "
"conceit for all external stimuli;"

msgctxt "an3.32:2.4"
msgid ""
"yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato "
"ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"upasampajja vihareyyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"and that they’d live having attained the freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom where ego, possessiveness, and underlying tendency to conceit are no "
"more.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.32:3.1"
msgid ""
"“Yathā kathaṃ pana, bhante, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā "
"imasmiñca saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu, bahiddhā ca "
"sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu;"
msgstr "“But how could this be, sir?”"

msgctxt "an3.32:3.2"
msgid ""
"yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato "
"ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"upasampajja vihareyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.133"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.32:4.1"
msgid "“Idhānanda, bhikkhuno evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "“Ānanda, it’s when a mendicant thinks:"

msgctxt "an3.32:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘etaṃ santaṃ etaṃ paṇītaṃ yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho "
"sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is peaceful; this is sublime—that is, the stilling of all activities, "
"the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, "
"cessation, extinguishment.’"

msgctxt "an3.32:4.3"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ kho, ānanda, siyā bhikkhuno tathārūpo samādhipaṭilābho yathā imasmiñca "
"saviññāṇake kāye ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu, bahiddhā ca "
"sabbanimittesu ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā nāssu;"
msgstr ""
"That’s how, Ānanda, a mendicant might gain a state of immersion such that "
"there’s no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to conceit for this "
"conscious body; and no ego, possessiveness, or underlying tendency to "
"conceit for all external stimuli;"

msgctxt "an3.32:4.4"
msgid ""
"yañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ upasampajja viharato "
"ahaṅkāramamaṅkāramānānusayā na honti tañca cetovimuttiṃ paññāvimuttiṃ "
"upasampajja vihareyyāti."
msgstr ""
"and that they’d live having achieved the freedom of heart and freedom by "
"wisdom where ego, possessiveness, and underlying tendency to conceit are no "
"more."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.32:5.1"
msgid "Idañca pana metaṃ, ānanda, sandhāya bhāsitaṃ pārāyane puṇṇakapañhe:"
msgstr ""
"And Ānanda, this is what I was referring to in ‘The Way to the Beyond’, in ‘"
"The Questions of Puṇṇaka’ when I said:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
#. VAR: paroparāni → parovarāni (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.32:6.1"
msgid "‘Saṅkhāya lokasmiṃ paroparāni,"
msgstr "‘Having considered the world high and low,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.32:6.2"
msgid "Yassiñjitaṃ natthi kuhiñci loke;"
msgstr "they’re not shaken by anything in the world."

#. <br>
#. VAR: anīgho → anigho (s1-3, km, pts1) | anagho (?)
msgctxt "an3.32:6.3"
msgid "Santo vidhūmo anīgho nirāso,"
msgstr "Peaceful, unclouded, untroubled, with no need for hope—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.32:6.4"
msgid "Atāri so jātijaranti brūmī’”ti."
msgstr "they’ve crossed over birth and old age, I declare.’”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.32:6.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
